{{Internet|expanded=General}}
'''網路中立性'''（'''net neutrality'''），亦稱為'''網際網路中立性'''（'''Internet neutrality'''），是一種[[原則|原則]]，要求[[網際網路服務供應商|網際網路服務供應商]]及政府應平等處理所有[[網際網路|網際網路]]上的資料，不差別對待或依不同用戶、內容、[[網站|網站]]、平臺、應用、接取裝置類型或通訊模式而差別收費。這一詞是由[[哥倫比亞大學|哥倫比亞大學]][[媒體法|媒體法]]教授[[吳修銘|吳修銘]]（Tim Wu）於2003年所提出，作為存在已久的[[公共運輸|公共運輸業者]]這個概念之延伸。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jthtl.org/content/articles/V2I1/JTHTLv2i1_Wu.PDF|title=Network Neutrality, Broadband Discrimination|publisher=Journal on telecom and high tech law|author=Tim Wu|year=2003|accessdate=2014-04-23|archive-date=2014-04-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140424062409/http://www.jthtl.org/content/articles/V2I1/JTHTLv2i1_Wu.PDF|dead-url=yes}}</ref><ref name=kraemer-def>{{cite journal en |author=Krämer, J |coauthors=Wiewiorra, L. & Weinhardt,C. |year=2013 |title=Net Neutrality: A progress report |journal=Telecommunications Policy |volume=37 |issue=9 |pages=794-813 |url=http://www.im.uni-karlsruhe.de/Upload/Publications/336c39b3-7a62-4159-bb1a-483f39dd5b24.pdf |accessdate=2015-09-18 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6YjuB9cRc?url=http://www.im.uni-karlsruhe.de/Upload/Publications/336c39b3-7a62-4159-bb1a-483f39dd5b24.pdf |archivedate=2015-05-23 }}</ref><ref name="berners-lee-def">{{cite web |url=http://dig.csail.mit.edu/breadcrumbs/node/144 |title=Net Neutrality: This is serious |accessdate=2008-12-26 |last=Berners-Lee |first=Tim |authorlink=Tim Berners-Lee |date=2006-06-21 |work=timbl's blog |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081227100511/http://dig.csail.mit.edu/breadcrumbs/node/144 |archivedate=2008年12月27日 }}</ref><ref name="nn-for-google-users">{{cite web |author=Staff |url= http://www.google.com/help/netneutrality.html |title=A Guide to Net Neutrality for Google Users |accessdate=2008-12-07 |publisher=[[Google|Google]] |deadurl=yes |archivedate=2008-09-01 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080901084929/http://www.google.com/help/netneutrality.html }}</ref>

一個常被引用來作為違反網路中立性原則的例子為，網際網路服務供應商[[Comcast|Comcast]]暗中利用偽造的數據封包減緩[[对等网络|P2P]][[檔案分享|檔案分享]]的上傳速率<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.msnbc.msn.com/id/21376597/|title=Comcast Blocks some Subscriber Internet Traffic, AP Testing shows|author=Peter Svensson|agency=Associated Press|date=2007-10-19|accessdate=2009-10-25|archive-date=2011-05-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110507232209/http://www.msnbc.msn.com/id/21376597/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。研究顯示，結合政策工具將有助於實現圍繞著網路中立性爭論的重要政治與經濟目標<ref name="ReferenceC">{{cite journal|last1=Bauer|first1=Johannes|last2=Obar|first2=Jonathan A.|title=Reconciling political and economic goals in the net neutrality debate|journal=Information Policy|date=2014|volume=30|issue=1|pages=1–19}}</ref>。

== 定義及相關原則 ==

=== 網路中立性 ===
網路中立性是一個原則，要求所有網際網路流量均應被平等對待<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.macworld.com/article/132075/2008/02/netneutrality1.html |title=Inside Net Neutrality: Is your ISP filtering content? |accessdate=2008-12-26 |last=Honan |first=Matthew |date=2008-02-12 |work=MacWorld |archive-date=2008-12-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081218093225/http://www.macworld.com/article/132075/2008/02/netneutrality1.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。據[[哥倫比亞大學法學院|哥倫比亞大學法學院]]教授[[吳修銘|吳修銘]]所述，解釋網路中立性的最好方法與設計網路時所期望的一樣：公眾資訊網路將在所有內容、網站及平臺被平等對待時達到其最佳的使用<ref name="wu-def">{{cite web |url=http://timwu.org/network_neutrality.html |title=Network Neutrality FAQ |accessdate=2008-12-26 |last=Wu |first=Tim |authorlink=Tim Wu |archive-date=2008-12-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081216141832/http://timwu.org/network_neutrality.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。在技術及服務上對網路中立性更詳細的定義為，服務的網路中立性意指，一個服務在某一層的運作不會影響到在該層上的其他服務，以僅依據該層所訂定的協議規範<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hbarel.com/analysis/policy/what-is-network-neutrality|title=Protecting Network Neutrality: Both Important and Hard|author=Hagai Bar-El|date=2014-08-19|accessdate=2014-08-19|archive-date=2014-08-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140820033907/http://www.hbarel.com/analysis/policy/what-is-network-neutrality|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

=== 開放網際網路 ===
開放網際網路的概念是指，網際網路的所有資源及操作這些資源的方式，能讓所有個人及企業都能輕易地取得。這通常包括網路中立性、[[開放標準|開放標準]]、[[透明化_(電信)|透明化]]、無[[網路審查|網路審查]]及低[[進入門檻|進入門檻]]等概念。開放網際網路這個概念有時會被解釋為[[權力分散|科技權力去中心化]]的理想，有些人並認為這個概念與[[開放原始碼軟體|開放原始碼軟體]]有著密切關連<ref>{{cite web|url=http://gigaom.com/2012/03/23/open-vs-closed-what-kind-of-internet-do-we-want/|title=Open vs. closed: What kind of internet do we want?|publisher=GigaOm|author=Mathew Ingram|date=2012-03-23|accessdate=2014-06-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171018233937/https://gigaom.com/2012/03/23/open-vs-closed-what-kind-of-internet-do-we-want/|archive-date=2017-10-18|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。

支持者通常會將網路中立性視為開放網際網路的重要部分，平等對待數據與開放[[網路標準|網路標準]]等政策，允許在網際網路上的人們能不受第三方干擾，輕易通訊與發展業務<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ec.europa.eu/digital-agenda/about-open-internet|title=About the Open Internet|publisher=European Commission|accessdate=2014-04-23|archive-date=2015-05-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150516122345/http://ec.europa.eu/digital-agenda/about-open-internet|dead-url=no}}</ref>。封閉網際網路則是指相反的情況，於此具有權限之個人、企業或政府能選擇偏好的使用方法。封閉網際網路可能會限制接取必要的[[網路標準|網路標準]]、[[流量塑形|人為降低]]部分服務的品質，或明確[[網際網路審查|過濾掉特定內容]]。

=== 笨水管 ===
{{Main|笨水管}}
由笨水管（dumb pipes）組成笨網路這個概念至少自1990年代初期就已經出現了。笨網路這個概念是指，網路的兩端通常會有具智能的人存在，而網路本身則留下對終端用戶通訊的管理及運作之功能。2013年，軟體公司MetroTech Net, Inc.提出笨電波（Dumb Wave）一詞，用來指笨水管這個概念在無所不在的行動網路上之應用。如果行動通訊業者不提供獨特的加值服務，他們將會降級到笨水道一層，而無法對加值服務收費，或無法留住用戶。

=== 終端對終端原則 ===
{{Main|終端對終端原則}}
終端對終端原則是一種網路設計原則，最初於1981年的會議裡，由[[傑瑞·薩特澤|傑瑞·薩特澤]]、[[大偉·派翠克·里德|大偉·派翠克·里德]]及[[大偉·克拉克|大偉·克拉克]]所寫的《系統設計的終端對終端議題》（End-to-end arguments in system design）中被明確提及。該原則敘述，只要可行，[[通訊協議|通訊協議]]的運作應被定義成發生在通訊系統的終端，或儘可能靠近所控制的資源。依據終端對終端原則，協議功能只有在需要性能最佳化時才能設定在系統最低層。因此，TCP重新傳輸（retransmission）為了其可靠性而做之設定仍是合理的，但應該在已達到最高的性能時停止再設定更多功能。該原則主張，可靠的系統會傾向需要終端對終端的處理能正確運作，除了其他在中介系統內的處理外。該原則指出，大多數在一通訊系統最低層的功能，都會對所有較高層的用戶端造成負擔，即使用戶端不需要這些功能；而若用戶端重新以終端對終端的方式實作了這些功能，這些功能就顯得多餘。這導致了一個具有智慧終端的最小化笨網路，與之前具有[[電腦端終|笨終端]]的智慧網路之架構完全地不同。
因為終端對終端原則是網際網路的核心設計原則，且因為實務上執行數據差別待遇的方法會違反終端對終端原則，該原則通常會在網路中立性的討論中被提及。終端對終端原則與網路中立性密切相關，且有時會被視為是網路中立性的前身<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.theatlantic.com/technology/archive/2014/04/the-best-writing-on-net-neutrality/361237/|title=Net Neutrality: A Guide to (and History of) a Contested Idea|publisher=The Atlantic|author=Alexis C. Madrigal and Adrienne LaFrance|date=2014-04-25|accessdate=2014-06-05|quote=This idea of net neutrality...[Lawrence Lessig] used to call the principle e2e, for end to end|archive-date=2021-03-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210315175106/https://www.theatlantic.com/technology/archive/2014/04/the-best-writing-on-net-neutrality/361237/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

=== 流量塑形 ===
{{Main|流量塑形}}
流量塑形是指為[[電腦網路|電腦網路]]流量進行控制，延緩符合特定條件之[[封包|封包]]的傳輸，以優化或保證性能、改善[[延遲_(電腦)|延遲]]，及/或增加可使用[[頻寬|頻寬]]<ref>[[:rfc:2475#section-2.3.3.3|IETF RFC 2475]] "An Architecture for Differentiated Services" section 2.3.3.3 – definition of "Shaper"</ref>。更具體地說，流量塑形是指對封包所作的任何行為，對這些封包施予額外的延遲，使其遵守一些預定的限制條件<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.itu.int/rec/T-REC-I.371-200403-I/en|title=ITU-T I.371 : Traffic control and congestion control in B-ISDN|author=tsbmail|publisher=|accessdate=2014-09-14|archive-date=2014-12-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141220063807/http://www.itu.int/rec/T-REC-I.371-200403-I/en|dead-url=no}}</ref>。流量塑形提供一種方法，以控制於特定期間內傳輸至[[電腦網路|網路]]的訊務之流量（[[頻寬調節|頻寬調節]]）、或傳輸流量的最大值（[[速率限制|速率限制]]），亦或者是[[通用細胞速率演算法|通用細胞速率演算法]]之類更複雜的規則。

=== 超額配置 ===
若一個網路的核心比被允許進入終端的訊務擁有更多的頻寬，則不需要流量政策即能獲得良好的服務品質。例如，電話網路使用允入控制（admission control），以拒絕對連線要求形成線路，限制用戶在網路上的需求。超額配置是[[統計分時多工|統計多工]]的一種，會寬鬆估算尖端時的用戶需求。超額配置被用在美國大學網路（如WebEx及[[美國的網路中立性|Internet 2 Abilene Network]]）等專用網路上。大衛·伊森伯格（David Isenberg）認為，持續性的超額配置總是能比服務品質或[[深度封包檢測|深度封包檢測]]技術花費更少費用而提供更多的容量<ref>{{cite web |url=http://isen.com/blog/2007/07/research-on-costs-of-net-neutrality.html |title=Research on Costs of Net Neutrality |accessdate=2008-12-26 |last=Isenberg |first=David |date=2007-07-02 |archive-date=2008-12-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081216143441/http://isen.com/blog/2007/07/research-on-costs-of-net-neutrality.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://arstechnica.com/articles/culture/Deep-packet-inspection-meets-net-neutrality.ars/3 |title=Deep packet inspection meets 'Net neutrality, CALEA |accessdate=2008-12-26 |last=Anderson |first=Nate |date=2007-07-25 |work=Ars Technica |archive-date=2009-01-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090123023226/http://arstechnica.com/articles/culture/Deep-packet-inspection-meets-net-neutrality.ars/3 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

== 相關議題 ==
=== 對協議差別待遇 ===
對協議差別待遇是指偏好或封鎖使用電腦用來通訊之[[通訊協議|通訊協議]]編碼的資料<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2008/08/02/technology/02fcc.html?_r=1|title=F.C.C. Vote Sets Precedent on Unfettered Web Usage|work=The New York Times|first=Saul|last=Hansell|date=2008-08-02|accessdate=2015-07-19|archive-date=2021-04-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210415141150/https://www.nytimes.com/2008/08/02/technology/02fcc.html?_r=1|dead-url=no}}</ref>。例如，Comcast於2008年故意阻擋部分用戶使用P2P檔案共享服務來下載大量檔案，FCC並因此對此事展開調查。後來，Comcast於2009年12月提議以每股16美元與FCC和解，但表示該公司沒有做錯事<ref>{{cite news|author=Duncan, Geoff|title=Comcast to Pay $16 Million for Blocking P2P Applications|url=http://www.digitaltrends.com/computing/comcast-to-pay-16-million-for-blocking-p2p-applications/|date=2009-12-23|publisher=Digital Trends|accessdate=2009-12-23|archive-date=2009-12-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20091225191525/http://www.digitaltrends.com/computing/comcast-to-pay-16-million-for-blocking-p2p-applications/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。然而，美國上訴法院於2010年4月判決FCC逾越其權限。為此，FCC的發言人耶恩·霍華德（Jen Howard）回應，「法院並沒有否定維持自由與開放網際網路的重要性，亦沒有關閉以其他方法達成此一重要目標的大門<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wsj.com/articles/SB10001424052702303411604575167782845712768|title=Court Backs Comcast Over FCC - WSJ|author=Amy Schatz|date=2010-04-07|work=WSJ|access-date=2015-07-19|archive-date=2021-04-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210415015933/https://www.wsj.com/articles/SB10001424052702303411604575167782845712768|dead-url=no}}</ref>。」儘管判決偏向Comcast一方，根據Measurement Lab於2011年10月的一份研究顯示，Comcast之後幾乎停止了對BitTorrent限速的所有措施<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wired.com/2011/10/bittorrent-throttling-comcast/|title=Comcast No Longer Choking File Sharers' Connections, Study Says - WIRED|work=WIRED|access-date=2015-07-19|archive-date=2021-04-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210429054632/https://www.wired.com/2011/10/bittorrent-throttling-comcast/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://torrentfreak.com/bittorrent-throttling-internet-providers-exposed-111020/|title=BitTorrent Throttling Internet Providers Exposed|work=TorrentFreak|accessdate=2015-07-19|archive-date=2017-08-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170808193441/https://torrentfreak.com/bittorrent-throttling-internet-providers-exposed-111020/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

=== 對IP位址差別待遇 ===
{{see also|IP封鎖|深度封包檢測}}
在網際網路的早期，產生一個非中立的網際網路在技術上是不可行的<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.freepress.net/sites/default/files/fp-legacy/Deep_Packet_Inspection_The_End_of_the_Internet_As_We_Know_It.pdf|title=Deep Packet Inspection: The end of the Internet as we know it?|publisher=Center for Internet and Society|author=M. Chris Riley and Ben Scott, Free Press|date=Mar 2009|accessdate=2014-05-29|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140909081342/http://www.freepress.net/sites/default/files/fp-legacy/Deep_Packet_Inspection_The_End_of_the_Internet_As_We_Know_It.pdf|archivedate=2014年9月9日}}</ref>。然而，網路安全公司[[NetScreen|NetScreen]]於2003年推出一款原本目的是用來過濾[[惡意軟體|惡意軟體]]的網路防火牆，稱之為[[深度封包檢測|深度封包檢測]]（deep packet inspection），使得對不同類型的資料採取即時的差別待遇變得可行<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.networkworld.com/news/2003/1020netscannou.html|title=NetScreen announces deep inspection firewall|publisher=Network World|author=Paul Roberts, IDG News Service|date=2003-10-20|accessdate=2014-05-29|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081207184318/http://www.networkworld.com/news/2003/1020netscannou.html|archivedate=2008年12月7日}}</ref>，且通常被用於[[網際網路審查|網際網路審查]]。

有些公司會不計入特定位址的數據用量，這樣在數據傳輸昂貴的地方就可以提升這些服務的競爭力，這種商業手段稱作[[零費率|零費率]]」，案例包括 Facebook Zero<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.engadget.com/2013/12/23/t-mobile-prepaid-free-facebook/|title=T-Mobile prepaid offering free data... but only to access Facebook|publisher=Engadget|author=Ben Gilbert|date=2013-12-23|accessdate=2014-11-18|archive-date=2019-06-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190608085500/http://www.engadget.com/2013/12/23/t-mobile-prepaid-free-facebook/|dead-url=no}}</ref>及Google Free Zone，在[[發展中國家|發展中國家]]尤其常見<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.slate.com/blogs/future_tense/2014/01/21/net_neutrality_internet_access_is_already_in_trouble_in_the_developing_world.html|title=Net Neutrality Is Already in Trouble in the Developing World|publisher=Slate|author=Lily Hay Newman|date=2014-01-21|accessdate=2014-11-18|archive-date=2014-11-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141116134940/http://www.slate.com/blogs/future_tense/2014/01/21/net_neutrality_internet_access_is_already_in_trouble_in_the_developing_world.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

有時，ISP 業者會針對那些在網路上產生龐大流量的服務供應者（而非其他人）收取費用。法國電信業者 Orange 抱怨從 YouTube 及其他 Google 網站流入的流量約占其網路整體流量的 50%，並與 Google 達成協議，就 Google 在其網路上產生之流量收取費用<ref>{{cite web |last=Robertson |first=Adi |url=http://www.theverge.com/2013/1/19/3894182/french-isp-orange-says-google-pays-to-send-traffic |title=French ISP Orange says it's making Google pay to send traffic over its network |publisher=The Verge |date=2013-01-19 |accessdate=2014-01-14 |archive-date=2021-04-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210415022721/https://www.theverge.com/2013/1/19/3894182/french-isp-orange-says-google-pays-to-send-traffic |dead-url=no }}</ref>。有些人認為 Orange 的競爭對手 Free 也會限制 YouTube 的流量。不過，法國電信監理機關所作的研究顯示，其網路只是單純在尖峰時段壅塞而已<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.arcep.fr/index.php?id=8571&L=1&tx_gsactualite_pi1%5Buid%5D=1619&tx_gsactualite_pi1%5Bannee%5D=&tx_gsactualite_pi1%5Btheme%5D=&tx_gsactualite_pi1%5Bmotscle%5D=&tx_gsactualite_pi1%5BbackID%5D=26&cHash=8d42d6993c018a12924d83cf72e3bd36|title=ARCEP closes the administrative inquiry involving several companies, including Free and Google, on the technical and financial terms governing IP traffic routing.|date=2013-07-19|accessdate=2014-01-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140201162548/http://www.arcep.fr/index.php?id=8571&L=1&tx_gsactualite_pi1%5Buid%5D=1619&tx_gsactualite_pi1%5Bannee%5D=&tx_gsactualite_pi1%5Btheme%5D=&tx_gsactualite_pi1%5Bmotscle%5D=&tx_gsactualite_pi1%5BbackID%5D=26&cHash=8d42d6993c018a12924d83cf72e3bd36|archive-date=2014-02-01|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。

=== 偏好專用網路 ===
網路中立的支持者認為，若不加以規範，網際網路服務供應商將能夠偏好他們自己的協議。ISP 將能透過利用專用網路區別哪些內容會被計入頻寬上限，來鼓勵用戶使用特定服務。

例如，Comcast 與微軟達成一項協議，允許其用戶透過 Xbox 360 上的 Xfinity 應用程式串流電視訊號，且不影響其頻寬限制。不過，用戶若使用其他視訊串流軟體，如 Netflix、HBO Go或  Hulu，則會被計入頻寬上限中。Comcast 否認該行為違反了網路中立性原則，因為「這項服務是在 Xbox 服務自身所擁有的專用網際網路協議網路上執行其Xfinity程式<ref>{{cite news |first=Dan |last=Mitchell |title=Is Comcast violating net-neutrality rules? |url=http://fortune.com/2012/05/16/is-comcast-violating-net-neutrality-rules/ |publisher=Fortune Magazine |date=2012-05-16 |accessdate=2015-09-18 |archive-date=2015-11-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151115140002/http://fortune.com/2012/05/16/is-comcast-violating-net-neutrality-rules/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

=== 對等互連差別待遇 ===
{{see also|對等互連}}
對於對等互連（peering）是否屬於網路中立性議題存在著一些爭議<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.businessweek.com/articles/2014-02-24/netflixs-deal-with-comcast-isnt-about-net-neutrality-except-that-it-is|title=Netflix’s Deal With Comcast Isn’t About Net Neutrality—Except That It Is|publisher=Bloomberg|author=Joshua Brustein|date=2014-02-24|accessdate=2014-11-18|archive-date=2014-09-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140915030202/http://www.businessweek.com/articles/2014-02-24/netflixs-deal-with-comcast-isnt-about-net-neutrality-except-that-it-is|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

2014年第1季，串流網站Netflix與ISP業者Comcast達成一項協議，以改善Netflix用戶端的服務品質<ref>{{cite news |first=Ryan |last=Waniata |title=Comcast Jumps up in Netflix Speed Rankings after Payola-style Agreement |url=http://www.digitaltrends.com/home-theater/comcast-jumps-netflix-speed-rankings-payola-style-agreement/ |publisher=Digital Trends |date=2014-04-14 |accessdate=2015-09-18 |archive-date=2020-10-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201014172920/https://www.digitaltrends.com/home-theater/comcast-jumps-netflix-speed-rankings-payola-style-agreement/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。這項協議是為了解決2013年間透過Comcast傳輸之速率越來越慢的問題，該年度的平均速率下滑了超過25%，來到史上最低點。在2014年1月達成協議後，Netflix的速率指數增加了66%。

Netflix於2014年與Verizon達成類似的協議，在Verizon DSL用戶的連線速率於該年稍早降至不到1Mbit/s以後。Netflix向所有使用Netflix服務，體驗低連線速率的Verizon用戶發送一份具有爭議的聲明，公開反對這項協議<ref>{{cite news |first=Ryan |last=Waniata |title=Netflix calls Verizon out on the big red screen [Update: Netflix backs off] |url=http://www.digitaltrends.com/home-theater/netflix-calls-verizon-right-big-red-screen/ |publisher=Digital Trends |date=2014-06-09 |accessdate=2015-09-18 |archive-date=2020-09-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200902195923/https://www.digitaltrends.com/home-theater/netflix-calls-verizon-right-big-red-screen/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。這引發兩家公司間的內部爭論，並讓Verizon於2014年6月5日取得[[停止並終止|禁止令]]（cease and desist order），以迫使Netflix停止散佈此訊息。

== 法律方面 ==
{{main|網路中立法}}

網路中立性原則在法律上的實現有許多種類型，從將對網際網路服務的封鎖與限速視為不合法的反競爭行為，至強制禁止公司偏好特定網路的網路應用<ref name="NYT-20150410">{{cite news |author=The Editorial Board |title=Editorial - Global Threats to Net Neutrality |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2015/04/10/opinion/global-threats-to-net-neutrality.html |date=2015-04-10 |work=[[New_York_Times|New York Times]] |accessdate=2015-04-10 |archive-date=2021-04-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210415033646/https://www.nytimes.com/2015/04/10/opinion/global-threats-to-net-neutrality.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。不同於大眾言論與仍對此一議題進行爭論的眾多人士，研究顯示單一政策工具（如不得封鎖政策或服務品質分層政策等）並無法達成該爭論核心的重要政治與經濟目標<ref name="ReferenceC"/>。Bauer及Ober表示，「保障多重目標需結合多項工具，包括政府及非政府的不同方法。此外，要促進言論自由、政治參與、投資與創新等目標，亦需要有各項配套的政策<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Bauer|first1=Johannes|last2=Obar|first2=Jonathan A.|title=Reconciling political and economic goals in the net neutrality debate|journal=Information Policy|date=2014|volume=30|issue=1|page=1}}</ref>。」

== 各国家和地区的網路中立性 ==
{{Further |網路中立法}}

=== 巴西 ===
{{main |巴西網際網路民權架構}}

巴西網際網路民權架構（[[葡萄牙語|葡萄牙語]]：Marco Civil da Internet）於2014年4月23日在[[全球網際網路治理大會|全球網際網路治理大會]]上進行討論時，成為法律。該法規範[[巴西網際網路|巴西網際網路]]的使用，規定使用網路者的期望原則、保障、權利及義務，並決定國家施政的準則<ref>{{cite news |first=Angelica |last=Mari |title=Brazil passes groundbreaking Internet governance Bill |url=http://www.zdnet.com/brazil-passes-groundbreaking-internet-governance-bill-7000027740/ |publisher=ZDNet |date=2014-03-26 |accessdate=2015-09-18 |archive-date=2014-10-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141025092023/http://www.zdnet.com/brazil-passes-groundbreaking-internet-governance-bill-7000027740/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://direitorio.fgv.br/noticia/the-brazilian-civil-rights-framework-for-the-internet |title=The Brazilian Civil Rights Framework for the Internet |accessdate=2015-09-18 |publisher=Fundação Getulio Vargas |date=2014-05-09 |archive-date=2015-05-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150514083732/http://direitorio.fgv.br/noticia/the-brazilian-civil-rights-framework-for-the-internet |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

=== 加拿大 ===
{{main |加拿大的網路中立性}}

2011年1月25日，加拿大廣播電視及電信委員會（CRTC）決定，可推出使用量計費方案<ref>[http://www.crtc.gc.ca/eng/archive/2011/2011-44.htm "Telecom Decision CRTC 2011-44"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.crtc.gc.ca/eng/archive/2011/2011-44.htm |date=20150316224937 }}, Canadian Radio-Television and Telecommunications Commission (CRTC), File number: 8661-C12-201015975, 25 January 2011.</ref>。
總理Harper表示政府會注意該項決定，「我們非常關心CRTC對用量計算的決定，以及該決定對消費者造成的影響。我已經要求應對該決定進行檢討<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.theglobeandmail.com/news/technology/tech-news/pm-orders-review-of-internet-billing/article1890567/ | location=Toronto | work=The Globe and Mail | first1=Steven | last1=Chase | first2=Iain | last2=Marlow | title=Harper steps into Web dispute - The Globe and Mail | date=2011-02-01 | accessdate=2015-07-19 | archive-date=2011-12-02 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111202070354/http://www.theglobeandmail.com/news/technology/tech-news/pm-orders-review-of-internet-billing/article1890567/ | dead-url=no }}</ref>。」有些人認為，該決定會對網路中立性有不利之影響，因為該決定會對聽訊及視訊等容量較大的媒體形成差別待遇<ref>{{cite web|last=Pinto|first=Lindsey|title=What does Usage-Based Billing mean for Net Neutrality?|url=http://www.saveournet.ca/content/what-does-usage-based-billing-mean-net-neutrality|accessdate=2011-07-04|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110828070723/http://www.saveournet.ca/content/what-does-usage-based-billing-mean-net-neutrality|archivedate=2011年8月28日}}</ref>。

=== 智利 ===
2010年6月13日，[[智利全國代表大會|智利全國代表大會]]修正電信法，以維護網路中立性，成為全球第一個立法的國家<ref>{{cite news |agency=Associated Press |url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/technology/2011/jun/23/netherlands-enshrines-net-neutrality-law |title=Net neutrality enshrined in Dutch law |work=The Guardian |date=2011-06-23 |accessdate=2011-06-23 |location=London |archive-date=2013-03-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130308121243/http://www.guardian.co.uk/technology/2011/jun/23/netherlands-enshrines-net-neutrality-law |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.elmundo.es/elmundo/2010/08/27/navegante/1282907501.html |title=Chile publica su ley que garantiza la neutralidad de la Red | Navegante |work=El Mundo |location=Spain |accessdate=2011-06-23 |archive-date=2011-08-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110821192544/http://www.elmundo.es/elmundo/2010/08/27/navegante/1282907501.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.elpais.com/articulo/sociedad/Quien/quiere/acabar/neutralidad/Red/elpepisoc/20100809elpepisoc_1/Tes|title=¿Quién quiere acabar con la neutralidad en la Red?|work=EL PAÍS|accessdate=2014-09-14|archive-date=2012-01-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120124134810/http://www.elpais.com/articulo/sociedad/Quien/quiere/acabar/neutralidad/Red/elpepisoc/20100809elpepisoc_1/Tes|dead-url=no}}</ref>。該法於2010年8月26日公布，對電信一般法（the General Law of Telecommunications）增定3項條文，禁止ISP業者隨意封鎖、干涉、歧視、妨礙或限制網際網路用戶使用、發送、接收或提供任何合法內容、應用、服務或其他於網際網路上合法之活動或用途的權利。ISP業者必須提供讓內容能不因其來源或擁有者不同即被隨意差別對待的網際網路接取服務<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.leychile.cl/Navegar?idLey=20453|title=Law 20,453|publisher=|accessdate=2014-09-14|archive-date=2014-08-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140816104919/http://www.leychile.cl/Navegar?idLey=20453|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

=== 印度 ===
{{Main|印度的網路中立性}}

直到2015年，[[印度|印度]]並沒有規範網路中立性的法律，且已有部分服務業者違反網路中立性。雖然[[印度電信監理局|印度電信監理局]]（TRAI）對統一接取服務執照的指導原則鼓勵網路中立性，但並不具強制力。[[2000年資訊科技法|2000年資訊科技法]]亦不禁止公司為其商業利益而限制他人服務<ref name=everything>{{cite news|title=Net Neutrality: Here is everything you need to know about it|accessdate=2014-09-29|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/technology/technology-others/net-neutrality/|work=[[The_Indian_Express|The Indian Express]]|date=2014-02-10|archive-date=2020-11-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201128232114/https://indianexpress.com/article/technology/technology-others/net-neutrality/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

2015年3月，TRAI就OTT服務的監理架構發布正式諮詢文件，尋求公眾意見。該諮詢文件被批評僅有單方面的看法，且敘述不清。該文件被許多政治家及網際網路用戶所譴責<ref name=Politicos>{{cite news|last1=Singh|first1=Saurabh|title=Politicos slam TRAI's stance on net neutrality|url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/technology/story/politicos-raise-concern-over-trais-threatening-consultation-on-net-neutrality/1/429135.html|accessdate=2015-04-12|work=[[India_Today|India Today]]|date=2015-04-08|archive-date=2015-04-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150412222226/http://indiatoday.intoday.in/technology/story/politicos-raise-concern-over-trais-threatening-consultation-on-net-neutrality/1/429135.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Gandhi|first1=Rajat|title=Net neutrality: Why Internet is in danger of being shackled|url=http://articles.economictimes.indiatimes.com/2015-04-08/news/60943272_1_net-neutrality-telecom-operators-viber|accessdate=2015-04-12|work=[[The_Economic_Times|The Economic Times]]|date=2015-04-08|archive-date=2016-01-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160110023114/http://articles.economictimes.indiatimes.com/2015-04-08/news/60943272_1_net-neutrality-telecom-operators-viber|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=TRAIemails>{{cite news|title=Indians rally for Internet freedom, send over 1 lakh emails to TRAI for net neutrality|url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/indians-rally-for-internet-freedom-send-over-1-lakh-emails-to-trai-for-net-neutrality/539553-11.html|accessdate=2015-04-13|work=[[IBNLive|IBNLive]]|date=2015-04-13|archive-date=2015-04-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150415193045/http://ibnlive.in.com/news/indians-rally-for-internet-freedom-send-over-1-lakh-emails-to-trai-for-net-neutrality/539553-11.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。直到2015年4月24日，已有超過100萬封電子郵件寄給TRAI，要求網路中立性<ref name=TRAIemails/><ref>{{cite web |title=India fights for #NetNeutrality |publisher=Cyber World Mirror |url=http://cyberworldmirror.com/india-fights-for-netneutrality/ |accessdate=2015-04-25 |archive-date=2015-05-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150503001041/http://cyberworldmirror.com/india-fights-for-netneutrality/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Roy|first1=Prasanto|title=India’s fight for net neutrality|url=http://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-india-32313704|publisher=BBC|accessdate=2015-04-18|location=India|date=2015-04-18|archive-date=2015-04-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150420153507/http://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-india-32313704|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Over 3 lakh emails sent to Trai in support of Net Neutrality, so far|url=http://tech.firstpost.com/news-analysis/over-3-lakh-emails-sent-to-trai-in-support-of-net-neutrality-so-far-263021.html|publisher=FirstPort|accessdate=2015-04-14|date=2015-04-14|archive-date=2015-04-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150414210848/http://tech.firstpost.com/news-analysis/over-3-lakh-emails-sent-to-trai-in-support-of-net-neutrality-so-far-263021.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

最近，[[美國聯邦通信委員會|美國聯邦通信委員會]]（FCC）通過「網路中立性」規則，禁止Comcast及Verizon等網際網路業者減緩或封鎖網路流量，或創造讓Netflix等內容業者付費使用的網際網路快車道。TRAI認為這是因為缺乏具體的「法治規則」。為了確保印度將來不會面臨到相同問題，TRAI及印度政府正在尋求明確界定可以做及不可以做之原則<ref>[http://tech.firstpost.com/news-analysis/govt-and-trai-looking-to-clearly-outline-rules-for-net-neutrality-law-in-india-report-265176.html "Govt and Trai looking to clearly outline rules for Net Neutrality law in India: report"] {{Wayback|url=http://tech.firstpost.com/news-analysis/govt-and-trai-looking-to-clearly-outline-rules-for-net-neutrality-law-in-india-report-265176.html |date=20160224070623 }}, Tech2 News, 28 April 2015.</ref>。

=== 荷蘭 ===
{{main |荷蘭的網路中立性}}

2012年6月4日，荷蘭成為歐洲第一個，以及接在智利以後世界第二個制定網路中立性法律的國家<ref name=stb-2012-235>{{cite journal|title=Wet van 10 mei 2012 tot wijziging van de Telecommunicatiewet ter implementatie van de herziene telecommunicatierichtlijnen|trans_title=Act of 10 May 2012 for the amendment of the Telecomminications Act for the implementation of the revised telecommunications directives|journal=Staatsblad van het Koninkrijk der Nederlanden|date=2012-06-04|volume=2012|issue=235|url=https://zoek.officielebekendmakingen.nl/stb-2012-235.html|accessdate=2014-02-10|language=nl|archive-date=2014-04-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140413181820/https://zoek.officielebekendmakingen.nl/stb-2012-235.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=guardian20110623>[http://www.theguardian.com/technology/2011/jun/23/netherlands-enshrines-net-neutrality-law "Net neutrality enshrined in Dutch law"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.theguardian.com/technology/2011/jun/23/netherlands-enshrines-net-neutrality-law |date=20210314182449 }}. ''The Guardian'' (London). Associated Press. 23 June 2011. Retrieved 3 April 2014.</ref><ref name=eff20120521>{{cite web|title=The Netherlands Passes Net Neutrality Legislation|url=https://www.eff.org/deeplinks/2012/05/netherlands-passes-net-neutrality-legislation|publisher=Electronic Frontier Foundation|accessdate=2014-02-10|date=2012-05-21|archive-date=2013-10-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131014150959/https://www.eff.org/deeplinks/2012/05/netherlands-passes-net-neutrality-legislation|dead-url=no}}</ref>。該法的主要條文要求「公眾電子通傳網路被用來提供網際網路接取服務之業者，以及網際網路接取服務之業者，將不得封鎖或減緩網際網路上的服務或應用」<ref name=Telecommunicatiewet7.4a>{{cite web|title=wetten.nl - Wet- en regelgeving - Telecommunicatiewet - BWBR0009950|trans_title=wetten.nl - Laws and policies - Telecommunications Act - BWBR0009950|url=http://wetten.overheid.nl/BWBR0009950/Hoofdstuk7/Artikel74a/geldigheidsdatum_10-02-2014|accessdate=2014-02-10|language=nl|at=Article 7.4a|archive-date=2015-03-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150315105419/http://wetten.overheid.nl/BWBR0009950/Hoofdstuk7/Artikel74a/geldigheidsdatum_10-02-2014|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

=== 美國 ===
{{Main |美國的網路中立性}}
在美國，對[[網路中立法|網路中立性是否需要以法律規定]]有著廣泛的辯論。網路中立性的支持者對寬頻業者使用其[[最後一哩|最後一哩]]網路封鎖網際網路應用與內容（如網站、服務及協議），甚至排除競爭對手的能力感到擾憂<ref>Lessig, L. 1999. [http://cyber.law.harvard.edu/works/lessig/www9.pdf Cyberspace’s Architectural Constitution] {{Wayback|url=http://cyber.law.harvard.edu/works/lessig/www9.pdf |date=20141225183518 }}, draft 1.1, Text of lecture given at www9, Amsterdam, Netherlands</ref> 。反對者則主張網路中立性管制會減損為了改善寬頻基礎建設的投資，而且是在修復不曾毀壞的某些事物<ref name="tiaonline.org">[http://www.tiaonline.org/sites/default/files/pages/Internet_ecosystem_letter_FINAL_12.10.14.pdf "Letter expressing strong opposition to proposals to classify broadband as a 'Title II' service"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.tiaonline.org/sites/default/files/pages/Internet_ecosystem_letter_FINAL_12.10.14.pdf |date=20150216163709 }}, to U.S. congressional leaders and members of the FCC", from representatives of a wide range of technology companies, 10 December 2014.</ref><ref name="chicagotribune.com">{{cite web|url=http://www.chicagotribune.com/news/opinion/commentary/ct-internet-regulations-fcc-ftc-obama-broadband-perspec-0219-20150218-story.html|title=The Internet isn't broken. Obama doesn't need to 'fix' it.|author=Chicago Tribune|date=2015-02-18|work=chicagotribune.com|accessdate=2015-07-19|archive-date=2015-02-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150226173240/http://www.chicagotribune.com/news/opinion/commentary/ct-internet-regulations-fcc-ftc-obama-broadband-perspec-0219-20150218-story.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

2015年2月26日，[[美國聯邦通信委員會|美國聯邦通信委員會]]（FCC）決定支持網路中立性，將寬頻接取服務重新歸類為電信服務，並因此將[[網際網路服務供應商|網際網路服務供應商]]納入[[1934年通傳法|1934年通傳法]][[公共運輸業者#電信|第2篇]]之適用範圍內<ref name="FCC-20150226">{{cite news |author=Staff |title=FCC Adopts Strong, Sustainable Rules To Protect The Open Internet |url=http://transition.fcc.gov/Daily_Releases/Daily_Business/2015/db0226/DOC-332260A1.pdf |format=[[PDF|PDF]] |date=2015-02-26 |work=[[Federal_Communications_Commission|Federal Communications Commission]] |accessdate=2015-02-26 |archive-date=2018-03-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180312162446/http://transition.fcc.gov/Daily_Releases/Daily_Business/2015/db0226/DOC-332260A1.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="NYT-20150226">{{cite news |last1=Ruiz |first1=Rebecca R. |last2=Lohr |first2=Steve |title=In Net Neutrality Victory, F.C.C. Classifies Broadband Internet Service as a Public Utility |date=2015-02-26 |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2015/02/27/technology/net-neutrality-fcc-vote-internet-utility.htm | work=[[New_York_Times|New York Times]] |accessdate=2015-02-26 }}</ref><ref name="AP-20150225">{{cite news |last=Flaherty |first=Anne |title=FACT CHECK: Talking heads skew 'net neutrality' debate |url=http://apnews.excite.com/article/20150225/us--net_neutrality-fact_check-e30cfb560f.html |date=2015-02-25 |work=[[AP_News|AP News]] |accessdate=2015-02-26 |archive-date=2017-12-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171227142926/http://apnews.excite.com/article/20150225/us--net_neutrality-fact_check-e30cfb560f.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="The FCC approves strong net neutrality rules">{{cite web | url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/the-switch/wp/2015/02/26/the-fcc-set-to-approve-strong-net-neutrality-rules/ | title=The FCC approves strong net neutrality rules | publisher=The Washington Post | date=2015-02-26 | accessdate=2015-02-26 | author=Fung, Brian | archive-date=2015-07-07 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150707230613/https://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/the-switch/wp/2015/02/26/the-fcc-set-to-approve-strong-net-neutrality-rules/ | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="FCC approves new net neutrality rules">{{cite web | url=http://www.usatoday.com/story/money/2015/02/26/fcc-approves-net-neutrality-rules/24053057/ | title=FCC approves new net neutrality rules | publisher=USA Today | date=2015-02-26 | accessdate=2015-02-26 | author=Yu, Roger and Snider, Mike | archive-date=2020-10-07 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201007003043/https://www.usatoday.com/story/money/2015/02/26/fcc-approves-net-neutrality-rules/24053057/ | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="HP-20150226">{{cite news |last=Liebelson |first=Dana |title=Net Neutrality Prevails In Historic FCC Vote |url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2015/02/26/net-neutrality-fcc-vote_n_6761702.html |date=2015-02-26 |work=[[The_Huffington_Post|The Huffington Post]] |accessdate=2015-02-27 |archive-date=2018-06-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180615181906/https://www.huffingtonpost.com/2015/02/26/net-neutrality-fcc-vote_n_6761702.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。2015年3月12日，FCC發布新網路中立性規則的具體細節<ref name="NYT-20150312a">{{cite news |last=Ruiz |first=Rebecca R. |title=F.C.C. Sets Net Neutrality Rules |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2015/03/13/technology/fcc-releases-net-neutrality-rules.html |date=2015-03-12 |work=[[New_York_Times|New York Times]] |accessdate=2015-03-13 |archive-date=2021-05-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210503092005/https://www.nytimes.com/2015/03/13/technology/fcc-releases-net-neutrality-rules.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="NYT-20150312b">{{cite news |last=Sommer |first=Jeff |title=What the Net Neutrality Rules Say |url=http://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2015/03/12/technology/net-neutrality-rules-explained.html |date=2015-03-12 |work=[[New_York_Times|New York Times]] |accessdate=2015-03-13 |archive-date=2021-05-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210505101543/https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2015/03/12/technology/net-neutrality-rules-explained.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="FCC-20150315">{{cite web |author=FCC Staff |title=Federal Communications Commission - FCC 15-24 - In the Matter of Protecting and Promoting the Open Internet - GN Docket No. 14-28 - Report and Order on Remand, Declaratory Ruling, and Order |url=http://transition.fcc.gov/Daily_Releases/Daily_Business/2015/db0312/FCC-15-24A1.pdf |date=2015-03-12 |format=[[PDF|PDF]] |work=[[Federal_Communications_Commission|Federal Communications Commission]] |accessdate=2015-03-13 |archive-date=2015-03-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150312200613/http://transition.fcc.gov/Daily_Releases/Daily_Business/2015/db0312/FCC-15-24A1.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>。2015年4月13日，FCC公布了新的法規<ref name="CNET-20150413">{{cite web |last=Reisinger |first=Don |title=Net neutrality rules get published -- let the lawsuits begin |url=http://www.cnet.com/news/fccs-net-neutrality-rules-hit-federal-register-lawsuit-underway/ |date=2015-04-13 |work=[[CNET|CNET]] |accessdate=2015-04-13 |archive-date=2015-04-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150414060656/http://www.cnet.com/news/fccs-net-neutrality-rules-hit-federal-register-lawsuit-underway/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="FR-20150413">{{cite web |author=[[Federal_Communications_Commission|Federal Communications Commission]] |title=Protecting and Promoting the Open Internet - A Rule by the Federal Communications Commission on 04/13/2015 |url=https://www.federalregister.gov/articles/2015/04/13/2015-07841/protecting-and-promoting-the-open-internet |date=2015-04-13 |work=[[Federal_Register|Federal Register]] |accessdate=2015-04-13 |archive-date=2015-05-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150502021951/https://www.federalregister.gov/articles/2015/04/13/2015-07841/protecting-and-promoting-the-open-internet |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

[[唐納德·川普|特朗普]]就任美國總統後，決定廢除網路中立性規則。2017年12月14日，[[美國聯邦通信委員會|美國聯邦通信委員會]]（FCC）通過廢除網路中立性規則的決議，放松对大型[[電信公司|电信公司]]的监管，使得这些公司对于网络用户能够看到什么拥有更大的操控权<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://theinitium.com/article/20171215-morning-brief/|title=美国联邦通信委员会废除“网络中立”规则|accessdate=|author=|date=2017-12-15|publisher=端傳媒 Initium Media|archive-date=2017-12-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171215111506/https://theinitium.com/article/20171215-morning-brief/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。[[美國西岸|美國西岸]]部分地方政府表明，不會接受聯邦通訊委員會投票決定，計劃上訴或在地方上繼續執行網路中立性規則<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://news.rthk.hk/rthk/ch/component/k2/1370261-20171215.htm|title=美國部分地方不滿網絡中立法遭撤銷　聲言要繼續執行|accessdate=|author=|date=2017-12-15|publisher=RTHK|archive-date=2017-12-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171215163756/http://news.rthk.hk/rthk/ch/component/k2/1370261-20171215.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.solidot.org/story?sid=54617 |title=Solidot {{!}} Cloudflare 探索方法降低 FCC 主席 Ajit Pai 家庭网络速度 |access-date=2017-11-25 |archive-date=2017-12-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171201031537/http://www.solidot.org/story?sid=54617 |dead-url=no }}</ref>2018年5月17日，美國參議院以52對47票表決通過，推翻[[聯邦通訊委員會|聯邦通訊委員會]]廢除網路中立性規則的決議，暫時擋住即將於6月生效的政策。<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.inside.com.tw/2018/05/17/u-s-senate-votes-to-overturn-fccs-repeal-of-net-neutrality-protections|title=|author=|date=|work=|accessdate=|archive-date=2018-07-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180706075729/https://www.inside.com.tw/2018/05/17/u-s-senate-votes-to-overturn-fccs-repeal-of-net-neutrality-protections|dead-url=no}}</ref>2020年10月27日，FCC以3-2投票废除网络中立性。<ref>{{Cite journal |date=2022-05-18 |title=Net neutrality in the United States |url=https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Net_neutrality_in_the_United_States&oldid=1088559972 |journal=Wikipedia |language=en}}</ref>新任总统乔·拜登于2021年7月9日签署特别行政令，要求FCC寻求重新建立网络中立性之方法。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Biden signs order to crack down on Big Tech, boost competition 'across the board'|url=https://www.cnbc.com/2021/07/09/biden-to-sign-executive-order-aimed-at-cracking-down-on-big-tech-business-practices.html|access-date=2022-05-31|date=2021-07-09|last=Feiner|first=Kevin Breuninger,Lauren|work=CNBC|language=en}}</ref>

=== 英國 ===
2007年，[[Plusnet|Plusnet]]使用[[深度封包檢測|深度封包檢測]]對P2P、[[檔案傳輸協議|檔案傳輸協議]]及線上遊戲等訊務進行限制及差別收費<ref>{{cite web |last=Anderson |first=Nate |url=http://arstechnica.com/hardware/news/2007/07/Deep-packet-inspection-meets-net-neutrality.ars/2 |title=Deep packet inspection meets 'Net neutrality, CALEA |publisher=Ars Technica |date=2007-07-25 |accessdate=2011-06-23 |archive-date=2012-04-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120411083032/http://arstechnica.com/hardware/news/2007/07/Deep-packet-inspection-meets-net-neutrality.ars/2 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。不過，Plusnet的網路管理政策明確標示於該公司所賣的各項方案中，並對不同網站採取一致之管制<ref>http://www.plus.net/support/broadband/speed_guide/traffic_management.shtml {{Wayback|url=http://www.plus.net/support/broadband/speed_guide/traffic_management.shtml |date=20141129021315 }} PlusNet: Broadband All about traffic management</ref>。

=== 中華民國 ===
2017年行政院通過「數位通訊傳播法」草案，限制數位通訊傳播服務提供者（ISP)對於數位通訊傳播網路通訊協定或流量管理，應以促進網路傳輸及接取之最佳化為原則，除法律另有規定外，不得附加任何顯失公平之限制。數位通訊傳播服務提供者應合理使用網路資源，除法律另有規定外，不得以其他技術或非技術之障礙干擾使用者之選擇。<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ey.gov.tw/Page/AE106A22FAE592FD/4f66d263-6c12-499c-b716-3e0483957aab|title=行政院草案|accessdate=|author=|date=|publisher=|archive-date=2020-09-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200923004806/https://www.ey.gov.tw/Page/AE106A22FAE592FD/4f66d263-6c12-499c-b716-3e0483957aab|dead-url=no}}</ref>

== 支持者的論點 ==
網路中立性的支持者包括消保團體、[[人權|人權]]組織、線上公司及部分科技公司<ref>{{cite web|title=Four tenors: Call for Internet Speech Rights|publisher=ARTICLE 19|url=http://www.article19.org/resources.php/resource/1776/en/four-tenors:-call-for-internet-speech-rights|accessdate=2012-08-31|archive-date=2012-09-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120903000748/http://www.article19.org/resources.php/resource/1776/en/four-tenors:-call-for-internet-speech-rights|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="meza">{{cite book |title=Coming Attractions? |last= Meza |first=Philip E. |authorlink= |coauthors= |year=|publisher= Stanford University Press|location= |isbn=<!--0-8047-5660-0 -->9780804756600|url=https://books.google.com/?id=QzMtQGPizqgC |page=158 |date=2007-03-20}}</ref>。許多大型網際網路應用公司是網路中立性的支持者。[[Yahoo!|Yahoo!]]、[[Vonage|Vonage]]<ref>{{cite book |title=Plunkett's Telecommunications Industry Almanac 2009 |last= Plunkett|first=Jack W. |authorlink= |coauthors= |year=2008 |publisher= Plunkett Research|location= |isbn=<!--1-59392-141-1 -->9781593921415|url=https://books.google.com/?id=6PUiN5cE7-QC&dq=%22data+prioritization%22+network+neutrality |page=208}}</ref>、[[eBay|eBay]]、[[亞馬遜公司|Amazon]]<ref>{{cite news |title=Defeat for net neutrality backers |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/technology/5063072.stm |publisher=BBC News |accessdate=2008-12-26 |date=2006-06-09 |archive-date=2008-12-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081226052628/http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/technology/5063072.stm |dead-url=no }}</ref>、[[IAC_(公司)|IAC/InterActiveCrop]]、[[微軟|微軟]]、[[Twitter|Twitter]]、[[Tumblr|Tumblr]]、[[Etsy|Etsy]]、[[Daily_Kos|Daily Kos]]、[[綠色和平|綠色和平]]及其他許多公司與團體，也都表示支持網路中立性<ref name="Open-Letter-to-Committee-Energy-Commerce">{{cite web |date=2006-03-01 |title=Open letter to the Committee on Energy and Commerce |url=http://static.publicknowledge.org/pdf/nn-letter-20060301.pdf |format=PDF |accessdate=2008-12-26 |postscript=<!--None--> |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060424065626/http://static.publicknowledge.org/pdf/nn-letter-20060301.pdf |archivedate=2006年4月24日 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.battleforthenet.com/sept10th/|title=Join the Battle for Net Neutrality|author=Fight for the Future|work=Battle For The Net|accessdate=2015-07-19|archive-date=2014-09-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140910235126/https://www.battleforthenet.com/sept10th/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。國際網際網路服務供應商[[Cogent_Communications|Cogent Communications]]發表聲明，表示該公司支持某一網路中立性政策<ref>{{cite web|author=Cogent Communications, Inc|authorlink=Cogent Communications|title=Net Neutrality Policy Statement|url=http://www.cogentco.com/us/NetNeutrality.php|accessdate=2009-04-21|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090418060408/http://www.cogentco.com/us/NetNeutrality.php|archivedate=2009年4月18日}}</ref>。2008年，Google公開表示該公司反對對寬頻業者濫用其市場力量，影響相競爭之應用或內容的接取。他們更進一步將網際網路與電話市場相類比，表示電話公司不會被允許控制其用戶的通話及通話內容<ref name="nn-for-google-users" />。不過，Google對網路中立性的支持在2014年遭到質疑<ref>{{cite web|url=http://gizmodo.com/googles-sordid-history-of-net-neutrality-hypocrisy-977444255/all|title=Google's Sordid History of Net Neutrality Hypocrisy|work=Gizmodo|accessdate=2014-09-14|archive-date=2019-08-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190805013610/https://gizmodo.com/googles-sordid-history-of-net-neutrality-hypocrisy-977444255/all|dead-url=no}}</ref>。[[美國公民自由聯盟|美國公民自由聯盟]]、[[電子前哨基金會|電子前哨基金會]]、[[Free_Press|Free Press]]及[[Fight_for_the_Future|Fight for the Future]]等部分人權組織亦支持網路中立性<ref name="Team-Internet">{{cite web | url=https://www.battleforthenet.com/teaminternet/ | title=Team Internet | publisher=[[Fight_for_the_Future|Fight for the Future]] | accessdate=2015-02-28 | archive-date=2016-01-02 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160102093757/https://www.battleforthenet.com/teaminternet/ | dead-url=no }}</ref>。

